The White House issued a Presidential Determination on September 8, 2009, regarding the eligibility of the Maldives to receive defense articles and defense services under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 and the Arms Export Control Act. The determination states that providing defense assistance to the Maldives will enhance the security of the United States and contribute to global peace. The Secretary of State is instructed to inform Congress of this determination and arrange for its publication in the Federal Register. The determination is signed by President Barack Obama.